findings.title: Most memorial highways honor Iraq and Afghanistan War veterans
findings.description: 100% of memorial highways in our current dataset commemorate service members who served in Iraq or Afghanistan conflicts.

findings.title: Army receives majority of memorial designations
findings.description: 67% of memorial highways honor Army service members, reflecting the branch's larger size and ground combat role.

findings.title: Geographic distribution is evenly spread
findings.description: Memorial highways are distributed across multiple regions with no single state dominating designations.
